fg_segments: As with most other websites, we collect and use the data contained in log files.

The information in the log files includes your IP (internet protocol) address, your ISP (internet service provider, such as AOL or BT), the browser you used to visit our site (such as Internet Explorer or Firefox), the time you visited our site and which pages you visited throughout our site.
The log files do not contain your name or email address.
As part of the forum registration process we collect your nickname and email address.
Your email address will only be used to send an optional email containing news about BrainDen.
You are under no obligation to enter your real details.

BrainDen website uses third party vendors, including Google, for some of its adverts, and as a third-party vendor, they use cookies to serve ads on BrainDen based on user's prior visits to both BrainDen and other sites.
Google's use of the DoubleClick DART cookie enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on your visit to sites on the Internet.
You may opt out of the use of the DoubleClick DART cookie by visiting the Google ad and content network privacy policy at http://www.google.co.uk/privacy_ads.html.
BrainDen website also uses other third-party advertising networks certified by Google (a list of which can be seen here https://www.google.com/adsense/support/bin/answer.py?answer=94149).
You may visit any of those websites to opt out of their cookies, if the vendor or ad network offers this capability.
You can opt out of some, but not all, of these cookies in one location at the Network Advertising Initiative opt-out website at http://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp.
We never sell any of your personal information to third parties.

raw_html:
Privacy Policy

Information Collection and Use

              As with most other websites, we collect and use the data contained in log files. The information in the log files includes your IP (internet protocol) address, your ISP (internet service provider, such as AOL or BT), the browser you used to visit our site (such as Internet Explorer or Firefox), the time you visited our site and which pages you visited throughout our site. The log files do not contain your name or email address.
              As part of the forum registration process we collect your nickname and email address. Your email address will only be used to send an optional email containing news about BrainDen. You are under no obligation to enter your real details.
              

Cookies

              BrainDen website uses third party vendors, including Google, for some of its adverts, and as a third-party vendor, they use cookies to serve ads on BrainDen based on user's prior visits to both BrainDen and other sites. Google's use of the DoubleClick DART cookie enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on your visit to sites on the Internet. You may opt out of the use of the DoubleClick DART cookie by visiting the Google ad and content network privacy policy at http://www.google.co.uk/privacy_ads.html.
              

Third Party Advertising

              BrainDen website also uses other third-party advertising networks certified by Google (a list of which can be seen here https://www.google.com/adsense/support/bin/answer.py?answer=94149). You may visit any of those websites to opt out of their cookies, if the vendor or ad network offers this capability. You can opt out of some, but not all, of these cookies in one location at the Network Advertising Initiative opt-out website at http://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp.
              

              We never sell any of your personal information to third parties.
              

              BrainDen - May 2012
